# Auth Rules

## Before touching auth code

Read ALL of:
- `proxy.ts` (middleware — the single enforcement point)
- `lib/admin.ts`
- `app/auth/callback/page.tsx`
- `app/admin/layout.tsx`
- `app/api/admin/session/route.ts`
- `app/logout/`

## proxy.ts is the single authority

Do not add auth logic elsewhere in middleware. All route gating and admin/customer routing lives in `proxy.ts`.

## Routing logic (proxy.ts)

```
Every request → apply security headers
/?code=...       → redirect /auth/callback (preserve query params, add next=/dashboard)
/welcome?sid=    → set ot_checkout_sid cookie, redirect /thank-you
/thank-you?sid=  → set ot_checkout_sid cookie, redirect /thank-you (strip param)
/login           → rate limit by IP
Customer route + admin session → redirect /admin
/upload or /admin/** + no session → redirect /login?redirectTo=<path>
```

## Admin detection (lib/admin.ts)

```ts
isAdminUser(userId, email)
// Reads ADMIN_OWNER_EMAILS (comma-separated, fallback: hardcoded email)
// Lowercase comparison on email
```

Called in three places only:
1. `proxy.ts` — checking customer routes
2. `app/admin/layout.tsx` — server-side on every admin page
3. Via `GET /api/admin/session` in `app/auth/callback/page.tsx`

## Auth callback (app/auth/callback/page.tsx)

Client component. After login:
1. `supabase.auth.getSession()` — verify session exists
2. `POST /api/thank-you/complete` — mark onboarding
3. `GET /api/admin/session` → `{isAdmin: bool}`
4. Admin → `router.replace('/admin')`, else → `router.replace(next)` (default: `/dashboard`)
5. No session → `router.replace('/login?error=oauth')`

## Admin layout (app/admin/layout.tsx)

Server component — double-checks auth on every admin page load:
- No session → `redirect('/login?redirectTo=/admin')`
- Not admin → `redirect('/dashboard?unauthorized=admin')`

## Supabase session clients

| File | Use |
|---|---|
| `lib/supabase-server.ts` → `createClient()` | Server Components, Route Handlers |
| `lib/supabase-admin.ts` → `getSupabaseAdmin()` | Admin, cron, webhook, worker — bypasses RLS |
| `lib/supabase/client.ts` → `createClient()` | Client Components (browser) |

Never mix these. Never use service role client-side.

## ot_checkout_sid cookie

Set by `proxy.ts` when `/welcome?sid=` or `/thank-you?sid=` is visited.
- httpOnly, secure, sameSite: lax, maxAge: 6h
- Consumed by `GET /api/thank-you/session`
- Used to link post-login state to the Stripe checkout session

## Logout

- Admin nav links to `/logout` (`<a href="/logout">`)
- `app/logout/` clears Supabase session server-side and redirects to `/`
- After logout, protected routes must redirect to `/login`

## Security headers (applied to every response by proxy.ts)

```
X-Frame-Options: DENY
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
Strict-Transport-Security (production only)
```
